values.Name: LoveDale Makalanga
values.Bio: LoveDale Makalanga, a Zimbabwean musician, composer, and producer, has spent over 17 years in the music industry. Raised in Harare, his love for music was nurtured by his father, a traditional mbira player, and his mother, a doylist. LoveDale's celebrated songs, like Ndizvo Chete and Chizevezeve, have earned him national recognition. As CEO of Muringa Music Factory, he strives to honor Zimbabwean expression. LoveDale is a graduate of Trust Academy and Music Crossroads, actively participates in cultural events, composes film scores, owns a record label, teaches music, and performs regularly. He also advocates for sustainable living as an ambassador for Zimbo Green Trust.

values.Name: Jon Dallas
values.Bio: Jon Dallas founded Real Talk Philosophy in Hanoi, Vietnam in March, 2017. Jon is a TEDx speaker, PADI SCUBA Dive Master, yoga instructor, and world traveler. He holds a BA in Theatre Performance from Towson University. Jon is originally from Jarrettsville, MD, USA, but lived for several years in Hanoi, Vietnam and Chiang Mai, Thailand. He now lives in Harare, Zimbabwe with his wife Jess. Find out more at jondallasjr.org.

values.Name: Hana Marie Smith
values.Bio: Hana Marie lives and works in Roanoke teaching pottery, outdoor education, and engaging unsuspecting denizens into discussions on a wide range of topics. Her undergraduate experience at Roanoke College in Philosophy and Political Science have helped nurture a strong passion for discussion and civic awareness. Her goal in working with RTP is to provide the foundation for members of a community to talk to one another rather than at one another.

values.Name: Shahin Kaveh
values.Bio:
Hi, my name is Shahin Kaveh. I have a B.Sc. in theoretical physics from Sharif University in Tehran, Iran. I have Master's degrees in philosophy from Texas Tech University (focused on Ethics and Aesthetics, resulting in an Ethics Certificate) and Johns Hopkins University (focused on systems of thought), as well as a PhD in History and Philosophy of Science from the University of Pittsburgh. I am a certified philosophical counselor and help people all over the world apply philosophy to their life problems and mental health issues.
​
I have founded several university organizations (including Real Talk @Pitt, and BridgePittsburgh) specifically aimed at bringing people together for civil disagreement, where I helped people practice one thing: perceiving contradictory information as a thrill, rather than a threat. I have a knack for making people comfortable with exploring ideas freely!
